credit_line: Gift of Mrs. Adrienne A. Sheridan
title: Sidewall
provenance: From the George Collins house (now Galle or Gallet) in Unionvale, Dutchess County, east of Poughkeepsie, built about 1840. Used in the bedroom of donor's great, great-grandfather's house (George Collins). See Property file for donor's letter.
description: Against a glazed white ground are printed regularly spaced clusters of conventionalized blossoms and foliage in two values of green. An all-over design of serpentine vines with small blossoms and foliage in gray is printed between the green clusters.
name: Sidewall
